 Uplevel Systems Raises $1.2M Funding to Launch New Managed Services Model to Small Business IT 
         










    










 













 











 



















Uplevel Systems Raises $1.2M Funding to Launch New Managed Services Model to Small Business IT Consultants
        																																												
              

          Hybrid Service Delivery Equips Consulting Firms to Remotely Manage Enterprise-class Wi-Fi, Data Security, Storage, and VPNs via the Cloud
        











 News provided by
Uplevel Systems  
Nov 17, 2016, 08:45 ET









 Share this article



























































TIGARD, Ore., Nov. 17, 2016 /PRNewswire/ -- Uplevel Systems, a provider of managed information technology (IT) services to small business IT consultants, today announced that the company has raised $1.2M in funding to launch and promote Uplevel's hybrid managed IT services to consultants targeting small businesses across the U.S.


Uplevel's hybrid approach to managed services combines advanced cloud-based management and enterprise-class equipment with delivery through a simple subscription that aligns to small businesses' specific needs and challenges.  This unique combination accommodates the budgets of smaller companies by eliminating up-front equipment expenses and enabling IT to be monitored and managed remotely by trusted IT experts.  The formal launch of services next month will include remote network management, wired and Wi-Fi networking, virtual private networks (VPNs), data backup and storage, firewall, and other enhanced data and network security services.
"With a solid track record of success in building new businesses, the founding team at Uplevel is now bringing disruptive technology to a large and underserved market," says Christopher A. DeMonico, investor and Board member. "The company's go-to-market strategy creates a compelling 'win-win' value proposition both for smaller businesses and the IT consultants who serve them. As Managed Service Providers (MSPs), consultants can grow their businesses faster and become more competitive while streamlining cost."
The Uplevel Systems founding team features proven technology innovators specializing in network management, Wi-Fi, and data security.  The team includes CEO Tom Alexander, former Chief Architect at PMC-Sierra who delivered the first fully integrated 8-port Ethernet switch; Vice President of Marketing Glenn Chagnot, former Director of Product Management and Marketing leader at Ixia and VeriWave, Inc.; and Product Architect Sergey Rathon, a twenty-year industry veteran specializing in delivering a high-quality user experience.
"By making it simple to deliver and support managed IT offerings, the Uplevel service delivery model equips IT consultants to provide more and better services to clients in the 5-25 employee segment, in less time and with less travel to customer sites," says CEO Tom Alexander. "And for the first time, smaller companies can benefit from business-grade technology and the peace of mind that comes with knowing trusted IT professionals are watching over their networks 24/7, without breaking the bank."
About Uplevel Systems
Founded in 2015, Uplevel Systems delivers managed IT services to small businesses through a channel of accomplished IT consultants nationwide. Uplevel's solutions combine enterprise-class networking - Ethernet, Wi-Fi, data backup and storage, firewall, and network security - with cloud-based management that allows IT consultants to deliver compelling IT services optimized for their smaller companies. Uplevel's hybrid managed services model combines powerful, remotely managed equipment installed at customer sites, with a subscription-based model that eliminates high up-front charges and is perfectly suited to small businesses. The Uplevel system keeps customer technology secure, current, and performing optimally at all times. www.uplevelsystems.com
Media Contact:Glenn Chagnot 133984@email4pr.com 817-898-0369
To view the original version on PR Newswire, visit:http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/uplevel-systems-raises-12m-funding-to-launch-new-managed-services-model-to-small-business-it-consultants-300364988.html
